abstract: Moving on several fronts toward shoring up support for his reelection bid, President Donald Trump capped off a busy Tuesday by heaping praise on the newest Republican member of Congress and savaging Democrats he said are engaged in “demented hoaxes” like his impeachment trial.
snippet: Moving on several fronts toward shoring up support for his reelection bid, President Donald Trump capped off a busy Tuesday by heaping praise on the newest Republican member of Congress and savaging Democrats he said are engaged in “demented hoaxe...
lead_paragraph: WILDWOOD, N.J. — Moving on several fronts toward shoring up support for his reelection bid, President Donald Trump capped off a busy Tuesday by heaping praise on the newest Republican member of Congress and savaging Democrats he said are engaged in “demented hoaxes” like his impeachment trial.
headline_main: Trump Shores Up Support for Newest GOP Congressman in Jersey
headline_print_headline: Trump Shores Up Support for Newest GOP Congressman in Jersey

abstract: Donald Trump Jr. hit the campaign trail Tuesday in Tennessee to help hammer home Republican Bill Hagerty's prevailing message in his campaign for the state's open U.S. Senate seat — that he's already scored President Donald Trump's endorsement.
snippet: Donald Trump Jr. hit the campaign trail Tuesday in Tennessee to help hammer home Republican Bill Hagerty's prevailing message in his campaign for the state's open U.S. Senate seat — that he's already scored President Donald Trump's endorsement.
lead_paragraph: GALLATIN, Tenn. — Donald Trump Jr. hit the campaign trail Tuesday in Tennessee to help hammer home Republican Bill Hagerty's prevailing message in his campaign for the state's open U.S. Senate seat — that he's already scored President Donald Trump's endorsement.
headline_main: Trump Jr. Boosts Hagerty for U.S. Senate in Tennessee Trip
headline_print_headline: Trump Jr. Boosts Hagerty for U.S. Senate in Tennessee Trip

abstract: President Trump’s lawyers finished their oral arguments, leaving senators the chance to ask questions of each side in the impeachment trial.

abstract: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said his government would effectively annex nearly a third of the occupied West Bank, with U.S. approval.
snippet: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said his government would effectively annex nearly a third of the occupied West Bank, with U.S. approval.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — The only immediate consequence of the Trump peace plan — and possibly all that will ever come of it — was the green light President Trump gave to Israel Tuesday to expand its territory by effectively annexing vast stretches of land it has long coveted on the West Bank.

abstract: Mr. Smith will leave the news organization where he has been editor in chief since 2012.
snippet: Mr. Smith will leave the news organization where he has been editor in chief since 2012.
lead_paragraph: Ben Smith, the editor in chief of BuzzFeed, who built a hard-hitting news operation within a digital media organization better known for clickbait and listicles, will be The New York Times’s next media columnist.

abstract: The Congressional Budget Office sees low interest rates, slow growth and big deficits through 2029.
snippet: The Congressional Budget Office sees low interest rates, slow growth and big deficits through 2029.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Congressional Budget Office predicted on Tuesday that the United States deficit will top $1 trillion annually over the next 10 years, ultimately reaching $1.7 trillion in 2030.

abstract: In what they acknowledged is a long-shot bid, West Virginia Gov. Jim Justice and Liberty University President Jerry Falwell Jr. urged unhappy Virginia counties Tuesday to secede and join a neighboring state where Democrats aren't in charge.
snippet: In what they acknowledged is a long-shot bid, West Virginia Gov. Jim Justice and Liberty University President Jerry Falwell Jr. urged unhappy Virginia counties Tuesday to secede and join a neighboring state where Democrats aren't in charge.
lead_paragraph: CHARLESTON, W.Va. — In what they acknowledged is a long-shot bid, West Virginia Gov. Jim Justice and Liberty University President Jerry Falwell Jr. urged unhappy Virginia counties Tuesday to secede and join a neighboring state where Democrats aren't in charge.
headline_main: Falwell and W.Va. Governor Pitch Virginia Secession Plea
headline_print_headline: Falwell and W.Va. Governor Pitch Virginia Secession Plea

abstract: President Donald Trump on Tuesday backed Secretary of State Mike Pompeo in Pompeo's battle with National Public Radio and tweeted out more media criticism, one target familiar and the other less so.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — President Donald Trump on Tuesday backed Secretary of State Mike Pompeo in Pompeo's battle with National Public Radio and tweeted out more media criticism, one target familiar and the other less so.

abstract: Lawyerly camaraderie was on full display, but some of the most intriguing interactions came from some of the senators themselves.
snippet: Lawyerly camaraderie was on full display, but some of the most intriguing interactions came from some of the senators themselves.
lead_paragraph: The body language in the Senate chamber spoke louder than words after President Trump’s team wrapped up its defense in his impeachment trial. This is what C-SPAN viewers did not see: Senator Dianne Feinstein, Democrat of California, bolted upright, looking startled, as Pat A. Cipollone, Mr. Trump’s personal lawyer, finished his closing statement. A murmur went up from the chamber as senators began rustling about. Finally, hour after hour, day after day of silence, senators could talk to one another.
